What you need to know:

External biosecurity is a raft of measures that a farmer implements on the farm to prevent diseases from outside from reaching the livestock.When you embrace external biosecurity, you focus on the critical areas of contamination of the farm from the outside world and execute measures to prevent disease-causing organisms from entering or leaving the farmVisitors bring pathogens or disease-causing organisms to your farm on their hands, clothes and feet.Animals such as dogs, cats, birds, insects and reptiles should be kept out of livestock houses. They carry a lot of pathogens that may cause diseases in your animals.